<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/4017a:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="to">Cole</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-31T16:00:00-05:00">January 31, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>29. For Murphy. The French have requested urgent consideration of a
                                quota for tractors, agricultural machinery and automobile spare
                                parts. Before examining this question further, the Department would
                                like to have an estimate of the situation from you, with particular
                                reference to the possibility of any such supplies or their
                                equivalents reaching the Axis forces in Libya.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>